# Performance Optimization

Optimize Angular applications for Core Web Vitals and smooth user experience.

## Default Behavior

### OnPush Change Detection (Required)

All components must use OnPush change detection strategy.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: OnPush strategy
@Component({
  selector: 'app-feature',
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  // ...
})
export class FeatureComponent {}
```

### Lazy Load Routes

All feature routes must be lazy loaded.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Lazy loaded routes
export const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: 'dashboard',
    loadComponent: () => import('./features/dashboard/dashboard.component')
      .then(m => m.DashboardComponent)
  },
  {
    path: 'products',
    loadChildren: () => import('./features/products/products.routes')
      .then(m => m.PRODUCT_ROUTES)
  }
];
```

### Debounce User Input

Debounce text inputs that trigger expensive operations.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Debounced search
toObservable(this.searchInput).pipe(
  debounceTime(300),
  distinctUntilChanged(),
  takeUntilDestroyed()
).subscribe(term => this.store.setSearchTerm(term));
```

### Track Items in Loops

Always use `track` in `@for` loops.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Track by unique identifier -->
@for (item of items(); track item.id) {
  <app-item-card [item]="item" />
}
```

### Use NgOptimizedImage

Use optimized image directive for all images.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Optimized images
import { NgOptimizedImage } from '@angular/common';

@Component({
  imports: [NgOptimizedImage],
  template: `
    <img ngSrc="/product.jpg" width="400" height="300" alt="Product" />
  `
})
```

## Rationale

1. **LCP (Largest Contentful Paint)** - Lazy loading and image optimization improve initial load.
2. **FID (First Input Delay)** - OnPush reduces unnecessary change detection cycles.
3. **CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift)** - Fixed image dimensions prevent layout shifts.
4. **Bundle size** - Lazy loading reduces initial bundle.

## Documented Exceptions

### 1. Priority Images (LCP Candidates)

Add `priority` attribute to above-the-fold images that are LCP candidates.

```html
<!-- ✅ Exception: Priority for hero/LCP images -->
<img 
  ngSrc="/hero.jpg" 
  width="1200" 
  height="600"
  priority
  alt="Hero image"
/>
```

### 2. Deferred Loading for Heavy Components

Use `@defer` for components below the fold or conditionally shown.

```html
<!-- ✅ Exception: Defer heavy components -->
@defer (on viewport) {
  <app-heavy-chart [data]="chartData()" />
} @placeholder {
  <app-chart-skeleton />
} @loading (minimum 200ms) {
  <app-loading-spinner />
}

<!-- ✅ Exception: Defer on interaction -->
@defer (on interaction) {
  <app-rich-editor />
} @placeholder {
  <textarea placeholder="Click to load editor..."></textarea>
}
```

### 3. Virtual Scrolling for Large Lists

Use CDK virtual scrolling for lists with 100+ items.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Virtual scroll for large lists
import { ScrollingModule } from '@angular/cdk/scrolling';

@Component({
  imports: [ScrollingModule],
  template: `
    <cdk-virtual-scroll-viewport itemSize="50" class="viewport">
      <div *cdkVirtualFor="let item of items(); trackBy: trackById" class="item">
        {{ item.name }}
      </div>
    </cdk-virtual-scroll-viewport>
  `
})
export class VirtualListComponent {
  trackById(index: number, item: Item): string {
    return item.id;
  }
}
```

### 4. Run Outside Angular Zone

For high-frequency events that don't need to trigger change detection.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Scroll handler outside zone
export class InfiniteScrollDirective {
  private readonly ngZone = inject(NgZone);
  
  constructor() {
    this.ngZone.runOutsideAngular(() => {
      fromEvent(window, 'scroll').pipe(
        throttleTime(200),
        takeUntilDestroyed()
      ).subscribe(() => {
        if (this.isNearBottom()) {
          this.ngZone.run(() => this.loadMore.emit());
        }
      });
    });
  }
}
```

### 5. Eager Loading for Frequently Used Routes

Preload routes that users typically visit.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Preload important routes
provideRouter(
  routes,
  withPreloading(PreloadAllModules)  // Or custom strategy
)

// Custom selective preloading
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class SelectivePreloadingStrategy implements PreloadingStrategy {
  preload(route: Route, load: () => Observable<any>): Observable<any> {
    return route.data?.['preload'] ? load() : of(null);
  }
}
```

## Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Missing OnPush
@Component({
  // No changeDetection specified = Default (bad)
})

// ❌ Triggering change detection in loops
export class BadComponent {
  constructor() {
    setInterval(() => this.checkSomething(), 1000);  // Triggers CD constantly
  }
}

// ❌ Scroll handlers in zone
fromEvent(window, 'scroll').subscribe(() => {
  // Triggers change detection on every scroll event
});

// ❌ Missing track in @for
@for (item of items()) {  // No track = poor performance
  <app-item [item]="item" />
}

// ❌ Importing entire libraries
import * as _ from 'lodash';  // Imports entire lodash

// ✅ Instead: Import specific functions
import { debounce } from 'lodash-es/debounce';

// ❌ Images without dimensions
<img src="/product.jpg" alt="Product" />  // Causes CLS
```

## Computed Signals for Memoization

Computed signals automatically memoize - use them for expensive derivations.

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Memoized expensive computation
expensiveComputation = computed(() => {
  const items = this.store.items();
  return items.reduce((acc, item) => {
    return acc + this.complexCalculation(item);
  }, 0);
});
```

## Bundle Optimization

### Tree Shaking

```typescript
// ✅ Tree-shakeable imports
import { map, filter } from 'rxjs/operators';
import { debounce } from 'lodash-es/debounce';

// ❌ Non-tree-shakeable
import * as rxjs from 'rxjs';
import _ from 'lodash';
```

### Code Splitting

Keep feature stores scoped to routes for better splitting.

```typescript
// ✅ Feature-scoped store
export const productRoutes: Routes = [{
  path: 'products',
  providers: [ProductStore],  // Scoped to this route
  loadComponent: () => import('./products.component')
}];
```

## Memory Management

### Cleanup Subscriptions

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Automatic cleanup
export class DataComponent {
  private readonly destroyRef = inject(DestroyRef);
  
  ngOnInit() {
    this.dataService.getData().pipe(
      takeUntilDestroyed(this.destroyRef)
    ).subscribe();
  }
}
```

### Avoid Closures Holding References

```typescript
// ❌ Closure keeps component alive
export class BadComponent {
  ngOnInit() {
    window.addEventListener('resize', () => {
      this.handleResize();  // 'this' holds reference
    });
  }
}

// ✅ Proper cleanup
export class GoodComponent implements OnDestroy {
  private resizeHandler = () => this.handleResize();
  
  ngOnInit() {
    window.addEventListener('resize', this.resizeHandler);
  }
  
  ngOnDestroy() {
    window.removeEventListener('resize', this.resizeHandler);
  }
}
```

## Core Web Vitals Targets

| Metric | Target | What It Measures |
|--------|--------|------------------|
| **LCP** (Largest Contentful Paint) | < 2.5s | Loading performance |
| **FID** (First Input Delay) | < 100ms | Interactivity |
| **CLS** (Cumulative Layout Shift) | < 0.1 | Visual stability |

## Checklist

- [ ] All components use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
- [ ] Routes are lazy loaded
- [ ] Heavy components use `@defer`
- [ ] Images use `NgOptimizedImage` with proper sizing
- [ ] LCP images have `priority` attribute
- [ ] Large lists use virtual scrolling
- [ ] Search inputs are debounced
- [ ] Scroll handlers run outside zone and are throttled
- [ ] All subscriptions are cleaned up
- [ ] Bundle is analyzed for unnecessary imports
